<br>
It is rather harsh to call a very valid argument 'drivel'.   The fact is that that drivel is the a very strong argument against your stance.  It is the core rebuttle to your argument.  There is not reason to remove the TLC. <br>
<br>
1) *Most* quests are discovered prior to the TLC, if you are looking for them?  <br>
2) There are valid and easy methods around the TLC:<br>
a) finding someone to get the componet for you (think of it as different form of a quest).  <br>
b) level down below the TLC<br>
c) merchant Mine.<br>
Yes, it may take work, but that is part of the Challenge.<br>
3) TLC does not stop the game.  If you can't get Uber item X, you can still continue to play.<br>
<br>
So basically, the TLC is just an obsticle.  It is part of FV, warts and all.<br>
<br>
You want some good reasons for the TLC? Ok, here:<br>
1) Creates NEW challenge.  New approaches to old problems.<br>
2) Encourages player cooperation.<br>
3) Helps to de-emphasis LEVEL goal orientation, and LEVEL status symbol (Thus, no more  I am Level 60, I can kill what I want, loot what I want, make what I want, etc.....). <br>
4) It helps keep the server population LOW. (And thus we have less Uber d00ds, Uber Guilds, etc.).  A Low server population also cuts down the amount of over camping, contested spawns, etc.  It might be a *challenge* to find a group and 'raids' may have to be rethought, but that is the fun of the FV server I LOVE.<br>
<br>
There is no reason to remove the TLC.  It is not 'broken'.  It does not stop game play.  It is just an obsticle.  Just because you cannot overcome an obsticle (which you knew was there and failed to plan ahead or think of an 'out of the box' solution) does not mean that it should be removed.  <br>
<br>
Are you going to say that the Sleeper needs to be nerfed or removed when you cannot over come it?  <br>
